10/

Day 8
Worsening cough, quite hacking now. Pain in chest due to coughing. Chest tight but monitoring sats. Will go in to hospital if they drop <95%. Staying in isolation. Worry about people with no sats probe and no medical training - how must they feel?

6/

Day 4
Awoke with the same symptoms - myalgia, pain behind eyes, tight chest. Temperature was 38.2 (the only raised temperature I've had). Still no cough. More fatigued today, slept lots.

9/

Day 7
Cough more pronounced today, painful in chest when coughing. Chest tighter again but relieved somewhat by salbutamol. Bad taste in mouth. No sense of smell at all. Have now reached the (UK) recommended period of self-isolation but still too ill to return to work.

7/

Day 5
Myalgia reduced. Headache still there, severe at times. Chest tight if I take a deep inspiration. First noticed my sense of smell has gone. Also lacking ability to taste anything. Occasional episodes of odd taste in the mouth. Still lacking the energy to do much.

Day 2
Had another episode of 'fever', but no temperature. Felt very cold, with muscle aches and headache. At this point I decided I was probably brewing COVID, despite still having no temperature and no cough. I just felt too unwell for it to be a simple cold.

2/

It's particularly interesting to me that I have had no cough (until recently) and no fever (apart from a single raised temperature). COVID can manifest in a variety of ways, so be alert to any change in normal.

Anyway, this has been my week...

I've just tested positive for COVID-19.

I'm an ED registrar in London who has treated many patients with COVID. I'm learning that it can present in a variety of ways.

I thought it would be useful to post about my symptoms so far, in the interests of better understanding.
